Al-Imdaad Foundation Project Coordinator, Suleman Dhanchora has given an  eyewitness account of what took place when the third earthquake struck in Türkiye. The country was hit by another earthquake on Monday night just two weeks after two earthquakes measuring 7.8 and 7.5 tore a path of destruction through Southern Türkiye and Northern Syria and killed nearly 46 000 people. The 6.4 magnitude quake that struck has its epicentre in Türkiye’s Hatay province which was the area worst affected by the largest quake 15 days ago. Türkiye’s interior minister said at least three people were killed and more than 200 were injured in the latest quakes. In the video below, Dhanchora describes what took place: